[:uniform metric:]

- Given some [[metric space]] $$(X, d)$$ and index set $$J$$, define the following [[metric]] on $$X^J$$ as:
    - $$\bar \rho(x, y) = \sup_{\alpha \in J}\bar d(x_\alpha, y_\alpha)$$
    - with $$\bar d(a, b)$$ the [[standard bounded metric]]
- Then $$\bar \rho$$ gives a [[metric topology]]; namely, the [[uniform topology]]
